messageBody:
On Jul 25, 2012, at 2:57 AM, "lee_zumbrunnen" <lee_zumbrunnen@...> wrote:
 

Is there available four line, color-coded paper. OR paper pads, OR spiral-bound notebooks to practice writing this form of alphabet, or does one need to make their own? _._,_.___

I have poor penmanship in _any_ writing system, so I started out by triple-spacing on wide-ruled paper. Once I got a bit better with the letterforms, I switched to triple-spaced college-ruled paper. Now I use double-spaced college-ruled paper.

Not sure what you'd want the color-coding for.
